{
  "$schema": "./sources.allowlist.schema (informal)",
  "$comment": "THE single enforced list of citeable domains for bucketmyfire content. Every external link in a published article (content/*.md) MUST resolve to a hostname that ends with one of these `domain` suffixes, or `verify:content` fails the build and the content engine's fact-check stage rejects the claim. This is the project's E-E-A-T / GEO moat: official sources only. Matching is hostname-suffix (so `cwfis.cfs.nrcan.gc.ca` matches `nrcan.gc.ca`). Tiers are honesty metadata, not gates: `government` = a gov-owned domain, `coordination` = the interagency centre that governments fund and report through, `authority` = a recognized non-profit program partnered with government (allowed, but say so). Seeded from src/three/livefire/official.ts + client.ts. To add a source: confirm it is genuinely a government / provincial / recognized-authority origin, add it here with a real label, and prefer a pure-gov (.gc.ca / provincial .ca) equivalent where one exists.",
